<!-- Retro-commissioning Section -->

<h2 id="retro-commissioning-introduction">A. Introduction</h2>
<p>
  This Retro-commissioning (RCx) report presents the findings of a retro-commissioning study conducted at
  {{project.property_address}}.
  This Retro-commissioning (RCx) report presents the findings of a retro-commissioning study conducted at
  {{project.property_address}}.
  The study includes an analysis of the building's systems, identification of operational improvements,
  and recommendations for implementation.
</p>

<h2 id="objectives">B. Objectives</h2>
<p>
  The objectives of the retro-commissioning study were to:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Identify and resolve operating problems in the building's systems</li>
  <li>Optimize the performance of existing equipment</li>
  <li>Improve occupant comfort and indoor air quality</li>
  <li>Reduce energy consumption and operating costs</li>
  <li>Extend equipment life</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="overview-of-results">C. Overview of Results</h2>
<p>
  The retro-commissioning study identified several opportunities for improving the operation of the building's systems.
  Implementation of the recommended measures is expected to result in annual energy savings of
  {{formatNumber rcxEnergySavings}} kWh and cost savings of {{formatCurrency rcxCostSavings}}.
</p>

